<subSubSection pageId="80" pageNumber="357" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="80.[2016,2610,1919,2337]" pageId="80" pageNumber="357">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2017,2172,1919,1944]" pageId="80" pageNumber="357">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Hartley, 1894" authorityName="Hartley" authorityYear="1894" box="[2185,2602,1919,1944]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="80" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albigula">Neotoma albigula Hartley, 1894</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation pageId="80" pageNumber="357">vicinity of Fort Lowell (near Tucson), Pima County, Arizona, USA</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="80" pageNumber="357" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="80.[2016,2610,1919,2337]" pageId="80" pageNumber="357">
Historically, 15 subspecies of N. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartley" authorityYear="1894" box="[2507,2610,2029,2062]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="80" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albigula">albigula</taxonomicName>
were recognized, but recent taxonomic revisions placed eastern and south-eastern populations (durangae, latifrons, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1894" box="[2492,2602,2151,2180]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="80" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucodon">leucodon</taxonomicName>
, melas, robusta, subsolana, and warreni) in N. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1894" box="[2073,2183,2234,2259]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="80" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucodon">leucodon</taxonomicName>
, and other authors placed south-western populations (
<taxonomicName box="[2425,2550,2265,2298]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="80" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanura">melanura</taxonomicName>
) in N. 
<taxonomicName box="[2059,2181,2308,2337]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="80" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanura">melanura</taxonomicName>
. Seven subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
